    "headline": "GameStop makes unsolicited offer to buy eBay for about $56 billion, WSJ reports",
    "summary": "GameStop has made an unsolicited offer to ‌acquire eBay Inc for about $56 ‌billion, the Wall Street Journal reported on ​Sunday, citing an interview with GameStop CEO Ryan Cohen.  GameStop has built a roughly 5% stake in ‌eBay and is ⁠offering $125 a share in cash and stock, Cohen ⁠told the WSJ.  The offer represents a premium of about ​20% to ​eBay's last ​closing price on ‌Friday.",
